snippet.title: ACMSIGGRAPH
snippet.description:
ACM SIGGRAPH is the Association for Computing Machinery's (ACM) Special Interest Group on Computer Graphics and Interactive Techniques (SIGGRAPH).

ACM SIGGRAPH is an international organization well-known for its annual conferences, SIGGRAPH and SIGGRAPH Asia. In addition to these major events, ACM SIGGRAPH has other committees which produce activities and conduct business throughout the year. These include the network of ACM SIGGRAPH Professional and Student Chapters, the Education Committee, the Digital Arts Committee and the Small Conferences Committee. For more information about these groups and all of our other activities, please visit our web site.
